## 🚀 **PRODUCT DEVELOPMENT WORKFLOW**

### **MANDATORY PRODUCT DEVELOPMENT SEQUENCE**

1. **📋 REQUIREMENTS ANALYSIS**
   - Gather stakeholder requirements
   - Conduct user research
   - Analyze business value
   - Define success metrics
   - Create requirements specification

2. **🏗️ DESIGN PHASE (MANDATORY)**
   - Create product vision and roadmap
   - Design user experience and interface
   - Define technical architecture
   - Create implementation plan
   - Get stakeholder approval

3. **💻 IMPLEMENTATION PHASE**
   - Coordinate with development teams
   - Monitor implementation progress
   - Ensure quality standards
   - Manage stakeholder expectations
   - Maintain documentation

4. **🧪 TESTING PHASE**
   - Coordinate user acceptance testing
   - Validate requirements implementation
   - Ensure quality standards
   - Manage stakeholder feedback
   - Prepare for launch

5. **📚 DOCUMENTATION PHASE**
   - Update product documentation
   - Create user guides and training
   - Document lessons learned
   - Prepare launch materials
   - Maintain knowledge base

6. **🚀 LAUNCH PHASE**
   - Execute go-to-market strategy
   - Monitor launch metrics
   - Collect user feedback
   - Iterate and improve
   - Plan next phase

